[[[break]]]changed line 29 from: *orange {code If people start spamming your wiki, and if they do it repeatedly from the same IP address, you can block their access.  Uncomment and edit the line {code blockIPAddresses} in config.io.  To block a single IP address, use a format like {code blockIPAddresses := "127.0.0.3"}.  To block a list of IP addresses, use a format like {code blockIPAddresses := "127.0.0.3|127.0.0.4|127.0.0.5"}.  To block a whole subnet, use a format like {code blockIPAddresses := "127.0.0.*"}.  Or you can give it any other regular expression.
}*[[[break]]]to: *green {code [This section is under construction.]

If a page is being spammed, you can lock it by adding its name to the file LockedPages.txt on the server.  Subsequently it can't be edited until it's unlocked (by --- you guessed it --- removing its name from that file).

I could implement more sophisticated spam-blocking mechanisms, and I've experimented with a few, but this is my favourite at the moment, for reasons which I hope to document later.  In particular, it's deliberate that users can't lock or password-protect their own pages.  The point is to encourage collaboration.
}*
